You need a extra tool for this function
install it with 
```bash
sudo apt install pcscd
sudo systemctl enable --now pcscd
```

Via cargo you need to install age-plugin-yubikey if you dont have cargo install this first with 
```bash
cargo install age-plugin-yubikey
```


When you are going to use age-encryption, you will need to configure a few things before you get started. It is extremely important to always first change your managemnt-key at the piv options.

The factory default management key from every yubikey is 010203040506070801020304050607080102030405060708 and you really need to change this!

There are two ways of generating a managemnt-key with or without  the --portect

With the protect option you let the yubikey generate it based on your pin
```bash
ykman piv access change-management-key --generate --protect
```

without the protect option the yubikeu  generates the key and you store it somewhere offline (on a usb or print it or create a qrcode from it)
```bash
ykman piv access change-management-key --generate
```
In my case it store the managemnt-key offline so i just run 
ykman piv access change-management-key --generate
and i keep the management-key somewhere safe.

Now you have to change the pin and puk code by

Change PIN with (default pin is 123456)
```bash
ykman piv access change-pin
```

Change PUK with (default puk is 12345678)
```bash
ykman piv access change-puk
```
Now you took all the masurements to copy the Identityfile (or private key) to your Yubikey.
now you can copy your age 
